Data are derived from California Office of Drinking Water (ODW) Water Quality Monitoring Database (WQMD, also know as Water Quality Inventory or WQI) and Permits, Inspection, Compliance, Monitoring, and Enforcement (PICME) database. The data set contains one record for each Community Water System (CWS) and includes additional detail about how many retail connections and how many people are served by each CWS.</dct:description>
